        "text": "Perfect! ✅ **Your LED blink circuit is ready!**\n\n## Summary\n**Circuit:**\n- **Red LED** connected to Arduino pin 13 (anode)\n- **220Ω current-limiting resistor** in series with the LED cathode\n- Resistor connects to GND (ground)\n\n**Sketch:**\n- Configures pin 13 as OUTPUT\n- Repeatedly turns the LED on for 1 second, then off for 1 second\n\n**How it works:**\nWhen you upload this sketch, the LED will blink continuously with a 1-second on/1-second off pattern. The 220Ω resistor limits the current to protect both the LED and the Arduino pin.\n\nYou can adjust the timing by changing the `delay(1000)` values (in milliseconds). For example, `delay(500)` would make it blink twice as fast!"
